We first notice that the “Initial” transactions (which have transaction date 2023‑12‑31 with types “Cash deposit”, “Bank deposit” and “Fixed Assets”) represent the initial paid‑in capital. Their amounts are:

• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 5,000,000.0  

Adding these up gives a total of 3,000,000 + 5,000,000 + 5,000,000 = 13,000,000.0 for the initial paid‑in capital.

Since none of the subsequent transactions (such as purchases, sales, expenses, depreciation, etc.) are related to capital injections or reductions (they affect other parts of the balance sheet or profit and loss), the paid‑in capital remains unchanged by the end of the period.

Thus, the initial and end values of the Paid‑in Capital are both 13,000,000.00.
